                <h1>When Was Lay's Founded? Discover the History of Lay's Chips</h1>
                <p>Lay's, a popular potato chip brand, was founded in 1932 by Herman Lay in Nashville, Tennessee. The brand originally started as a small operation selling handmade chips from the back of a car. Over the years, Lay's expanded dramatically, becoming a household name with its wide variety of flavors and snack options.</p>
